.Method : enum

Enum with the methods of authentication supported by Carbon LDP.

Enumeration Description
CarbonLDP.Auth.Method.BASIC

HTTP Basic authentication sending the username and password in every call.
CarbonLDP.Auth.Method.TOKEN

Authentication with username and password generating a token that will be sent in every call.

carbonldp/HTTP/HTTPMethod
Module

Default Export:
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod

.HTTPMethod : enum

Enum with the HTTP/1.1 methods.

Enumeration Description
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod.OPTIONS

Enum that identifies the OPTIONS HTTP/1.1 method, which allows the client to determine the options and/or requirements associated with a resource, or the capabilities of a server, without implying a resource action or initiating a resource retrieval.
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod.HEAD

Enum that identifies the HEAD HTTP/1.1 method, which returns only the headers of a GET HTTP request.
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod.GET

Enum that identifies the GET HTTP/1.1 method, which returns whatever information is identified by the request URI.
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod.POST

Enum that identifies the POST HTTP/1.1 method, which requests to the server to create a new entity.
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod.PUT

Enum that identifies the PUT HTTP/1.1 method, which allows you to replace an entirely entity, or to send a signal to a resource.
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod.PATCH

Enum that identifies the PATCH HTTP/1.1 method, which allows you to update specified fields of an entity.
CarbonLDP.HTTP.HTTPMethod.HTTPMethod.DELETE

Enum that identifies the DELETE HTTP/1.1 method, which allows you to request the deletion of a resource identified by the request URI.

#setPreferredRetrieval() : CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions 


setPreferredRetrieval( retrievalType:"representation" | "minimal", requestOptions:CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions ):CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions

Set a Prefer header which indicates to the platform to type of retrieval to make.


Param Type Default Description
retrievalType "representation" | "minimal"

If "representation" is chosen the platform must retrieve the entire resource; otherwise when "minimal" is sent the minimal data will be returned generally an empty one.
requestOptions CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions


#setRetrievalPreferences() : CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions 


setRetrievalPreferences( preference:CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RetrievalPreferences, requestOptions:CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions, returnRepresentation?:boolean ):CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions

Set a Prefer header with return=representation in an options object request.


Param Type Default Description
preference CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RetrievalPreferences
requestOptions CarbonLDP.HTTP.Request.RequestOptions
returnRepresentation boolean

If set to true, add return=representation; before include and/or omit. Default value is set to true.

.headers : Map<string, CarbonLDP.HTTP.Header.Header>

A map object containing the headers returned by the request.


.request : XMLHttpRequest | ClientRequest

The XMLHttpRequest object that was provided in the constructor when working in a Browser, or the ClientRequest object when working with Node.js.


.status : number

The status code returned by the request.

schema CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.DigestedObjectSchema

The schema of the resource to create its delta.
oldResource CarbonLDP.Resource.Resource

The old representation of the resource to create the delta.
newResource CarbonLDP.Resource.Resource

The current representation of the resource to create the delta.


.getPatch() : string 


getPatch():string

Returns the LD Patch string of the resources provided in addResource method.

carbonldp/Messaging/Service
Module

Default Export:
CarbonLDP.Messaging.Service.MessagingService

Classes

C
CarbonLDP.Messaging.Service.MessagingService
Class that manages the messaging client, connecting and subscriptions.




CarbonLDP.Messaging.Service.MessagingService
Class

Class that manages the messaging client, connecting and subscriptions.


Constructor 


MessagingService( context:CarbonLDP ):void

Param Type Default Description
context CarbonLDP

Methods

.connect() : void 


connect( onConnect?:() => void, onError?:( error:Error ) => void ):void

Connect to the Platform messaging broker. Is the Service is already connected, an error will be thrown.


Param Type Default Description
onConnect () => void

Callback to be invoked when the client has established a connection. It will be invoked again when a reconnection has been executed.
onError ( error:Error ) => void

Callback to be invoked when a error has occurred in the connection or server. If none is provided, the errors will be broadcasted to every connected subscription.


.reconnect() : void 


reconnect( onConnect?:() => void, onError?:( error:Error ) => void ):void

Reconnect the service to the Platform broker. If the service is already connected, it will be closed and opened again.


Param Type Default Description
onConnect () => void

Callback to be invoked when the client has established a connection. It will be invoked again when a reconnection has been executed.
onError ( error:Error ) => void

Callback to be invoked when a error has occurred in the connection or server. If none is provided, the errors will be broadcasted to every connected subscription.


.setOptions() : void 


setOptions( options:CarbonLDP.Messaging.MessagingOptions ):void

Update the messaging service options. If any property is no defined the default is used:

{
																    maxReconnectAttempts: 10,
																    reconnectDelay: 1000
																}
																```.

Param Type Default Description
options CarbonLDP.Messaging.MessagingOptions

The options to be updated


.subscribe() : void 


subscribe( destination:string, onEvent?:( message:CarbonLDP.Messaging.EventMessage.EventMessage ) => void, onError?:( error:Error ) => void ):void

Subscribe to an event described by the destination provided.


Param Type Default Description
destination string

The destination of the event to subscribe for.
onEvent ( message:CarbonLDP.Messaging.EventMessage.EventMessage ) => void

Callback to be invoked in every notification event and will be provided with the data message of the event.
onError ( error:Error ) => void

Callback to be invoked when a error has occurred in the subscription.


.unsubscribe() : void 


unsubscribe( destination:string, onEvent?:( message:CarbonLDP.Messaging.EventMessage.EventMessage ) => void ):void

Remove the subscription set for the specific destination and onEvent callback.


Param Type Default Description
destination string

The destination of the subscription to be removed.
onEvent ( message:CarbonLDP.Messaging.EventMessage.EventMessage ) => void

Callback of the subscription to be be removed.




carbonldp/Messaging/Utils
Module

Methods

#createDestination() : void 


createDestination( event:string, uriPattern:string, baseURI:string ):void

Create a 'topic' destination using the event and the URI pattern provided. This pattern is parsed with the carbonldp/Messaging/Utils#parseURIPattern method. If invalid event of URI is given an error will be thrown.


Param Type Default Description
event string

The event of the destination messaging notification.
uriPattern string

The URI pattern of the destination messaging notification.
baseURI string

The base URI where the URI of the pattern belongs to.


#parseURIPattern() : void 


parseURIPattern( uriPattern:string, baseURI:string ):void

Parse the provided URI pattern that follows a more glob-like syntax to the AMQP path syntax.


Param Type Default Description
uriPattern string

The URI pattern to be transformed.
baseURI string

The base URI where the URI of the patten belongs to. This is used to obtain the the relative path that AMQP requires.


#validaEventType() : void 


validaEventType( event:string ):void

Test if the provided string is a valid Messaging event. If don't an error will be thrown.


Param Type Default Description
event string

The event to be evaluated.

validateEventContext( context:CarbonLDP.Context.Context ):void

CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.DigestedObjectSchema
Class

Class of a standardized Schema that is used for the SDK for compact and expand JSON-LD objects and Carbon Resources.


Properties

.base : string

The base URI of the schema.


.language : string

The default language of the string properties.


.prefixes : Map<string, string>

Map that contains the prefixes of absolutes URIs.


.properties : Map<string, CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.DigestedObjectSchemaProperty>

Map that contains the definitions of the properties in the schema.


.vocab : string

URI that will be used to resolve properties URIs that aren't defined in the schema.





CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.DigestedObjectSchemaProperty
Class

Class for standardized object properties of a schema.


Properties

.containerType : CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.ContainerType

The type of container the property is. It's null if the property is no container type.


.language : string

The language the property is in.


.literal : boolean

Indicates if the property is a literal or not.


.literalType : string

The type of literal the property is. It's null if the property is not a literal.


.uri : string

The absolute URI that represents the property





CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.ObjectSchema
Interface

Interface that represents an schema based in the JSONLD contexts. This is used to convert from the JSONLD stored in the server to the Documents used in the SDK and vice versa.


Properties

.@base : string

An absolute URI that is used to resolve relative URIs. If it's set to null, will invalidate a previous @base value.


.@index : object

[Not Supported] This element is ignored.


.@language : string

The default language of the string properties.


.@reverse : object

[Not Supported] This element is ignored.


.@vocab : string

An absolute URI that is used to as the common prefix for all the relative properties. If it's set to null, will invalidate a previous @vocab value.


.[ name:string ] : (string | CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.ObjectSchemaProperty)

This index can be interpreted in two forms:

  • As a prefix: When the value is as string. The name is taken a a prefix and the string value must be an absolute URI.
  • As a property: When the value is of type CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.ObjectSchemaProperty. The name is taken as the name of the property.




CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.ObjectSchemaDigester
Class

Class with functions to standardize a JSON-LD Context Schema.

CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.ObjectSchemaProperty
Interface

Interface that defines the property of a schema.


Properties

.@container : string

If the property is multiple it can be of tree types:

  • @set: An unsorted array of elements.
  • @list: An sorted array of elements
  • @language: An string property with multiple languages.

.@id : string

The absolute URI of the property in the JSONLD which is mapped to the key name where this definition was referred.


.@language : string

The language of the property.


.@type : string

If the property is a literal, this specifies its XSD type.

CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.ObjectSchemaUtils
Class

Methods

#resolveURI() : string 


resolveURI( uri:string, schema:CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.DigestedObjectSchema, relativeTo?:{ vocab?:boolean, base?:boolean } ):string

Tries to resolve a non absolute URI using the schema and the configuration provided.


Param Type Default Description
uri string

The URI to ve resolved.
schema CarbonLDP.ObjectSchema.DigestedObjectSchema

The schema where to find the prefixes or the default vocabulary to utilize.
relativeTo { vocab?:boolean, base?:boolean }

An additional configuration object to specify the resolution mode of a relative URI, where the vocab takes priority before the base.

carbonldp/SPARQL/QueryDocument/QueryPropertySchema
Module

Default Export:
CarbonLDP.SPARQL.QueryDocument.QuerySchemaProperty.QuerySchemaProperty

Interfaces

I
CarbonLDP.SPARQL.QueryDocument.QuerySchemaProperty.QuerySchemaProperty
Interface that describes an property to retrieve in a partial query creation.




CarbonLDP.SPARQL.QueryDocument.QuerySchemaProperty.QuerySchemaProperty
Interface

Interface that describes an property to retrieve in a partial query creation.


Properties

.@container : @set | @list | @language

The container type the property will be interpreted to have.

  • @set: An unordered array of elements- @list: An ordered array of elements.- @language: An object map with the language as key and the string content as the value.

.@id : string

The URI that the actual property has in the platform.


.@language : string

The only specific language of a string primitive to be retrieved.


.@type : @id | string

The type of property. If @id is used, it will represent a Pointer. For an literal it will generally expect the absolute XSD type URI, but a relative one can also be assigned. e.g. string will be interpreted as http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string.


.query : ( queryBuilder:CarbonLDP.SPARQL.QueryDocument.QueryDocumentBuilder.QueryDocumentBuilder ) => CarbonLDP.SPARQL.QueryDocument.QueryDocumentBuilder.QueryDocumentBuilder

Function to build a query to specify sub-properties or when retrieving multiple resources to filter the resources.
